16:00.427 --> 16:02.460
- Where are you staying?

16:02.562 --> 16:04.295
- Uh, just been, uh,

16:04.397 --> 16:07.031
crashing in my truck
        for a while now.

16:07.133 --> 16:09.667
- Are you serious?
I--I have a bedroom here

16:09.769 --> 16:13.438
if you--if you'd
like to stay here.

16:13.540 --> 16:15.707
- Look, um...

16:15.809 --> 16:18.643
I know this is a lot.

16:18.745 --> 16:21.546
You don't gotta try
                     to be nice.

16:21.648 --> 16:23.014
I just wanted to see

16:23.116 --> 16:26.684
if you were anything
           like what I remember.

16:26.786 --> 16:28.453
You don't owe me nothing.

16:28.555 --> 16:32.390
- Matty.
Matty?

16:32.492 --> 16:35.126
You can't just go.

16:35.795 --> 16:39.163
I'd like you to meet Ian
and his wife, Rachel,

16:39.265 --> 16:43.134
so if you don't have
any other plans...

16:44.738 --> 16:47.672
Why don't you just stay?

16:47.774 --> 16:50.708
- I don't want to impose.
            - Please.

16:50.810 --> 16:57.915
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:01.921 --> 17:03.921
[sighs]

17:06.593 --> 17:08.893
I can't believe this.

17:10.597 --> 17:13.998
So this is not much.

17:14.099 --> 17:16.666
- Oh, trust me, it, uh--
               it beats sleeping

17:16.770 --> 17:18.970
in my truck seat.
         [both chuckle]

17:19.973 --> 17:22.406
- Well, I'll see you
            in the morning then.

17:24.176 --> 17:27.779
You used to like the door open
           when you were little.

17:27.881 --> 17:30.915
Shall I--
           - Close it.

17:31.017 --> 17:32.383
- Okay.

17:32.485 --> 17:35.353
- Hey, Mom?

17:35.455 --> 17:36.954
Uh...

17:37.057 --> 17:39.957
wow, um, sorry.

17:40.060 --> 17:43.194
It--it just sort
 of slipped out.

17:43.296 --> 17:45.596
- You can call me
              whatever you want.

17:46.466 --> 17:48.933
- Thanks for all this.

17:49.035 --> 17:51.169
- Goodnight.

17:51.271 --> 17:58.309
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:11.357 --> 18:13.724
- [exhales]

18:21.734 --> 18:28.773
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:47.160 --> 18:48.659
- How do you like the food?

18:48.761 --> 18:50.194
- Delicious.
             - Okay?

18:50.296 --> 18:52.630
- Thank you.
    - It's really good, Mom.

18:56.903 --> 19:00.805
- So, uh, Mom's not the only
   successful one in the family.

19:00.907 --> 19:03.241
- Ah, well, no, it's--

19:03.343 --> 19:06.878
- Ian, uh, started his own
  company when he was just 17,

19:06.980 --> 19:09.380
and he sold it last year.

19:09.482 --> 19:10.848
- Yeah.
             - Hmm.

19:10.950 --> 19:12.083
- Six figures.
             - Mom.

19:12.185 --> 19:14.352
- What?
    I can't say six figures?

19:14.454 --> 19:16.187
- Wow.
       - High six figures.

19:16.289 --> 19:17.555
- Mom, come on.

19:17.657 --> 19:20.091
- No, you got to be
                  proud of that.

19:20.193 --> 19:22.927
I mean, money like that

19:23.029 --> 19:25.329
changes your life.

19:25.431 --> 19:26.864
- Yeah.

19:26.966 --> 19:29.634
- I mean,
      I--I wouldn't know, but...

19:32.872 --> 19:37.041
- Ian--Ian actually co-owns
a venture capital company now.

19:37.143 --> 19:39.343
- He sure does.
       - Tell him, honey.

19:39.445 --> 19:42.513
- Oh, um, yeah...
[stammers]

19:42.615 --> 19:45.383
We invest in
              a lot of startups,

19:45.485 --> 19:47.552
like, you know,
       different tech companies.

19:47.654 --> 19:49.520
It's...

19:51.191 --> 19:53.391
- That's really something.

19:53.493 --> 19:56.360
AI mean, impressive, I mean.

19:56.462 --> 19:58.262
- Thanks.
     - Well, I--I never had

19:58.364 --> 20:00.198
much of a head for that,

20:00.300 --> 20:03.768
you know, the--
 the stocks and business stuff.

20:03.870 --> 20:06.571
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

20:06.673 --> 20:13.611
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:13.713 --> 20:15.479
- Yeah, I mean,
              you should come by

20:15.582 --> 20:16.948
and visit the office next week.

20:17.050 --> 20:18.482
I'd--I'd love
to show you around,

20:18.585 --> 20:21.619
and I could buy you lunch,
           and, um...

20:21.721 --> 20:23.554
Come on, we got a lot
           of catching up to do.

20:23.656 --> 20:26.891
- Sure.
                  I'd like that.

20:27.627 --> 20:30.528
- [sighing]

20:30.630 --> 20:33.497
<i> [tense music]</i>

20:33.600 --> 20:40.671
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:58.758 --> 21:01.659
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

21:01.761 --> 21:04.996
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:05.098 --> 21:08.132
[leaves rustling]

21:17.477 --> 21:18.809
[screams]

21:18.911 --> 21:20.244
- [stammers]
                   I'm so sorry.

21:20.346 --> 21:22.146
I saw you walking
             towards the window.

21:22.248 --> 21:23.481
- No, it's fine.

21:23.583 --> 21:24.649
- I thought something
                      was wrong.

21:24.751 --> 21:26.150
- Uh, it's--it's okay.
I--

21:26.252 --> 21:28.886
- Here, let me--
   - No, please, it's my mess.

21:28.988 --> 21:31.889
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

21:31.991 --> 21:34.492
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:34.594 --> 21:36.827
- Well, uh...

21:36.929 --> 21:40.231
I'm, uh, sorry again.

21:46.973 --> 21:48.205
- Thank you.

21:48.308 --> 21:49.940
- No, of course
you're confused.

21:50.043 --> 21:51.742
I can't imagine what you must
be going through right now.

21:51.844 --> 21:52.910
- It's not that
            I don't believe him.

21:53.012 --> 21:54.545
I want to.

21:54.647 --> 21:56.881
It just--the timing,

21:56.983 --> 21:59.283
it's just strange.

21:59.385 --> 22:01.018
- It's strange?

22:01.120 --> 22:04.588
But, you know, life has a way
of doing that, right?

22:04.691 --> 22:08.759
- I guess. It just complicates
     everything with the estate.

22:08.861 --> 22:10.227
- You're worried
about the money?

22:10.330 --> 22:13.397
- No, no,
      I--I don't need the money,

22:13.499 --> 22:15.433
and Matt has every right
                   to his share,

22:15.535 --> 22:17.768
I mean, especially after
   everything he's been through,

22:17.870 --> 22:20.538
but the fact
          that he shows up now--

22:22.375 --> 22:24.809
- Look, I have a detective
 friend in the department.

22:24.911 --> 22:27.278
If you want, I could ask him
to do some digging,

22:27.380 --> 22:30.314
see if there are any
red flags in Matt's history.

22:32.518 --> 22:34.218
You don't have to tell him,

22:34.320 --> 22:36.354
but you do have
a right to know.

22:39.058 --> 22:40.958
- So we started two years ago
         with just, uh,

22:41.060 --> 22:43.594
me and my two partners working
     out of this strip mall dump

22:43.696 --> 22:46.130
that smelled like a--
               an old fish tank,

22:46.232 --> 22:48.566
and, uh, now we have
                   35 employees,

22:48.668 --> 22:52.036
and everything just
           keeps getting better.

22:53.906 --> 22:56.407
And here we are.

22:57.343 --> 22:59.744
- Wow.
         - Not bad, huh?

22:59.846 --> 23:02.012
- It's something else, man.
          - [chuckles]

23:02.115 --> 23:04.248
- And you got all these people
              working under you?

23:04.350 --> 23:06.317
Doing whatever you want?

23:06.419 --> 23:08.285
That's the dream, right?

23:08.388 --> 23:11.122
Hey, half those guys
     are old enough to be a dad.

23:11.224 --> 23:13.023
Must drive them nuts.

23:13.126 --> 23:17.027
- Yeah, but I mean, the resume
 means more than the birthday,

23:17.130 --> 23:19.964
well, especially in tech,
   which is where we're focused.

23:20.066 --> 23:23.000
It's actually something
I wanted to talk to you about.

23:23.102 --> 23:25.069
Got a few minutes?

23:25.905 --> 23:29.807
So I had my eye on this,
        uh, new startup,

23:29.909 --> 23:31.542
this--this little company
                     in Portland

23:31.644 --> 23:33.110
that's gonna completely change

23:33.212 --> 23:35.279
the way people think
       about home entertainment.

23:35.381 --> 23:38.449
I'm talking, like, what Apple
 did for the cell phone market.

23:38.551 --> 23:40.851
It's a game-changer,

23:40.953 --> 23:44.955
and...I haven't even
              brought it up here

23:45.057 --> 23:47.391
because...

23:47.493 --> 23:51.462
well, between the inheritance
   and the--the insurance money,

23:51.564 --> 23:53.431
there's more than enough
          to go in on this thing

23:53.533 --> 23:55.900
completely independent.

23:59.405 --> 24:01.338
- With your money, you mean?

24:01.441 --> 24:02.673
- Yeah, well, that--
     that's what I'm saying.

24:02.775 --> 24:04.175
I want you to come in
on it with me

24:04.277 --> 24:06.210
and watch this thing
blow up together.

24:06.312 --> 24:08.012
- No, I--
    - Hey, come on, come on.

24:08.114 --> 24:09.513
Just listen to me.

24:09.615 --> 24:12.650
- Sorry, but...
This ain't my world.

24:12.752 --> 24:13.918
- That's why I'll take care
                  of everything.

24:14.020 --> 24:15.186
I'll manage it.
I'll do all the work,

24:15.288 --> 24:16.253
60-40 split...
        - Thanks, but no.

24:16.355 --> 24:17.488
- Of a 51% share.

24:17.590 --> 24:18.889
Wait, Matt,
will you just listen?

24:18.991 --> 24:20.691
Imagine owning 20% of Facebook.

24:20.793 --> 24:22.827
- I said no.

24:22.929 --> 24:25.830
<i> [tense music]</i>

24:25.932 --> 24:27.331
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:27.433 --> 24:29.166
I'm sorry.

24:29.268 --> 24:31.602
It's just not for me.

24:31.704 --> 24:34.138
I've been sleeping
               in my truck, man.

24:35.475 --> 24:38.542
You can't possibly know
               what that's like.

24:38.644 --> 24:40.077
Look, I'm never
              gonna be like you,

24:40.179 --> 24:41.579
and I'm okay with that.

24:41.681 --> 24:43.948
All I want is
              whatever I'm owed.

24:44.050 --> 24:45.950
In cash.

24:46.052 --> 24:47.885
Just keep it simple.

24:47.987 --> 24:52.056
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:52.158 --> 24:53.624
- So what about his story,
                           okay?

24:53.726 --> 24:55.426
He said he was brought
                  to St. John's?

24:55.528 --> 24:57.461
You know they have to report
  that to the local authorities.

24:57.563 --> 25:00.097
I mean, some kid named Matt was
   turned in 40 miles from here,

25:00.199 --> 25:02.132
and you didn't hear about it?
      It doesn't make any sense.

25:02.235 --> 25:03.434
- I--I don't know.
   - I don't think you should

25:03.536 --> 25:04.935
let him stay here.
             - Ian.

25:05.037 --> 25:07.204
- No, I'm serious.
          Ev--even if it is him,

25:07.306 --> 25:09.039
you don't know anything
         about him, not really.

25:09.141 --> 25:10.708
What if he's dangerous?

25:10.810 --> 25:12.776
- What if he's your brother
who we left for dead

25:12.879 --> 25:15.112
and tried to forget about?

25:18.351 --> 25:20.117
- [sighs]
                    Let's just--

25:20.219 --> 25:22.920
let's get him to do
                   the DNA test.

25:23.022 --> 25:25.456
Until then be careful.

25:25.558 --> 25:27.224
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:04.397 --> 26:06.997
[door creaks]

26:18.711 --> 26:21.445
- Hey.

26:21.547 --> 26:23.948
- Hey.

26:24.050 --> 26:25.349
Sorry it's so late.

26:25.451 --> 26:28.319
- Where were you?

26:28.421 --> 26:31.221
- Just, uh--just out.

26:31.324 --> 26:33.824
I, uh--I went for a long drive.

26:33.926 --> 26:35.559
- Mm-hmm.
       - I was just trying

26:35.661 --> 26:38.996
to process everything,
                       you know?

26:39.098 --> 26:40.698
- Listen, there's something
       that we have to do

26:40.800 --> 26:43.334
for the probate court.
   It's--it's not a big deal.

26:43.436 --> 26:46.303
We just have to prove
     your identity to the judge,

26:46.405 --> 26:50.074
so there's this kit, um.

26:50.176 --> 26:54.378
- You want me
       to take a DNA test?

26:54.480 --> 26:56.714
- It's--it's not a big deal.

26:58.250 --> 27:00.284
- You don't believe me.

27:00.386 --> 27:03.921
- No, it's not that at all.

27:05.925 --> 27:08.192
- Look, I don't have to be here
          if you don't trust me.

27:08.294 --> 27:12.663
- No, it--it's just a--
      a stupid legal thing.

27:12.765 --> 27:14.898
- All you have to do
   is tell them I'm your son.

27:15.001 --> 27:17.401
- It's not that simple.

27:17.503 --> 27:19.436
- Does Ian have to do it?

27:22.308 --> 27:25.042
- Ian's situation is
     a lot different than yours.

27:25.144 --> 27:28.278
- Yeah, tell me about it.

27:28.381 --> 27:31.081
- Matt.

27:31.183 --> 27:34.051
<i> [dark music]</i>

27:34.153 --> 27:41.191
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:54.740 --> 27:57.307
- Hey, it's Karen.
       Leave me a message.

27:57.410 --> 27:59.743
- Hey, uh, Kare, it's me.
      Listen, I got to run.

27:59.845 --> 28:03.514
Um, I'm gonna leave you a key
      under the front mat,

28:03.616 --> 28:07.551
and there may still be somebody
 working here when you get here,

28:07.653 --> 28:09.486
so I'll let her know
    that you're on your way.

28:09.588 --> 28:11.221
Uh, let's get together
           this week.

28:11.323 --> 28:13.357
I've got a lot to tell you.

28:13.459 --> 28:16.326
Bye.

28:16.429 --> 28:18.395
Hey, Jess?
      - Yeah? You leaving?

28:18.497 --> 28:20.364
- Yeah, uh, listen,
         somebody might swing by

28:20.466 --> 28:22.032
to look at the house for a bit.

28:22.134 --> 28:24.034
Um, she can let herself in,

28:24.136 --> 28:26.336
but if you leave,
      just feel free to lock up.

28:26.439 --> 28:28.605
- Okay, you got it.
Hey.

28:28.708 --> 28:31.809
Say hi to Matt for me.

28:33.612 --> 28:37.214
<i> - ♪ Mother Nature's</i>
         <i> got it right ♪</i>

28:37.316 --> 28:41.452
<i> ♪ Every time she shines</i>
 <i> her big ole light down on me ♪</i>

28:41.554 --> 28:44.688
<i> ♪ You know I'm feeling fine ♪</i>

28:44.790 --> 28:47.157
<i> ♪ When I walk outside ♪</i>

28:47.259 --> 28:52.096
<i> ♪ To see blue skies... ♪</i>

28:52.198 --> 28:54.531
- Hello?
         - Hey, in here.

28:54.633 --> 28:57.201
- Oh, hi.
      I'm Sarah's sister-in-law.

28:57.303 --> 28:59.069
I'm just gonna take
                  a peek around.

28:59.171 --> 29:01.405
<i> - ♪ Blue skies and sunshine ♪</i>

29:01.507 --> 29:03.040
- Wow.

29:03.142 --> 29:06.443
This is a great space, huh?

29:06.545 --> 29:09.446
- Yeah, you sure get
  a lot of light in this room.

29:09.548 --> 29:11.648
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

29:11.751 --> 29:13.817
- Jessie?

29:13.919 --> 29:15.919
Jessie Parker, is that you?

29:16.021 --> 29:19.056
My God, I haven't seen you
              since high school.

29:19.158 --> 29:21.391
- Right, Karen.
What--

29:21.494 --> 29:24.628
- Oh, what are
             the chances, right?

29:25.898 --> 29:29.800
Yeah, um, Sarah said
            I'd like this place.

29:29.902 --> 29:34.338
It's, uh--it's a lot bigger
        than I expected.

29:34.440 --> 29:37.975
Oh, my God, wait a minute.
 You're working for Sarah?

29:38.077 --> 29:40.511
Isn't that weird with
the whole you and Jake history?

29:40.613 --> 29:43.680
[coughing]

29:43.783 --> 29:45.616
[grunts]

29:45.718 --> 29:48.619
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

29:48.721 --> 29:49.753
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:49.855 --> 29:52.723
[yelps, straining]

29:52.825 --> 29:59.863
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:05.104 --> 30:06.837
- I hope you still like meat.

30:06.939 --> 30:09.039
- Mm, yeah, whatever
     that is smells amazing.

30:09.141 --> 30:10.607
- Yeah, you probably
                  remember this.

30:10.709 --> 30:13.610
It was your dad's
          favorite chili recipe.

30:13.712 --> 30:15.379
You used to love it.

30:15.481 --> 30:18.115
- Oh, I, uh--
I did the DNA thing.

30:18.217 --> 30:19.650
- Really?

30:19.752 --> 30:21.351
- Yeah, turned it
in this afternoon.

30:21.453 --> 30:23.787
- Yeah?

30:23.889 --> 30:26.290
- I didn't mean to be
so whatever about it.

30:27.660 --> 30:29.526
I felt this weirdness
between us.

30:29.628 --> 30:31.461
I don't want that.

30:31.564 --> 30:34.298
- I don't want that either.

30:34.400 --> 30:36.066
I was thinking about
           reaching out to your,

30:36.168 --> 30:38.368
uh--your foster parents.

30:38.470 --> 30:41.872
I mean, they know
           everything about you,

30:41.974 --> 30:45.409
things that you may not
        even remember, you know?

30:45.511 --> 30:46.910
I'd--like, I want to know
                what it was like

30:47.012 --> 30:48.979
when you lost your first tooth,

30:49.081 --> 30:51.682
you got your first report card.

30:51.784 --> 30:55.185
Did you like sports?
   Did you have the chicken pox?

30:55.287 --> 30:58.088
You know, things like that.

30:59.425 --> 31:01.325
They have this whole
            lifetime of memories

31:01.427 --> 31:03.227
that I've missed out on,

31:03.329 --> 31:06.997
and I just want to soak it up.
    That's not a problem, is it?

31:07.099 --> 31:08.765
I mean, you're still
                close with them?

31:08.868 --> 31:11.501
- Yeah, um, it's--
[chuckles]

31:11.604 --> 31:13.370
It's just a little weird
for me.

31:13.472 --> 31:15.572
- The Reynolds family, right?

31:15.674 --> 31:19.209
- Ann Reynolds.
It's just her now.

31:19.311 --> 31:22.479
Tim left the picture
a few years ago.

31:22.581 --> 31:24.781
He and I were never that close.

31:37.296 --> 31:39.096
Here's her number.

31:39.198 --> 31:40.898
I think you'll like her.

31:41.000 --> 31:42.900
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

31:43.002 --> 31:44.801
<i> [voicemail beeps]</i>
           - Hi, Ann.

31:44.904 --> 31:48.038
This is, uh,
         Sarah Sherwood.

31:48.140 --> 31:50.774
I'm not sure
   how much Matt has told you,

31:50.876 --> 31:53.210
but, um...

31:53.312 --> 31:55.879
I'm his mother.

31:55.981 --> 31:57.447
I'm sorry.
     This is sort of strange

31:57.549 --> 31:59.049
to leave on a message.

31:59.151 --> 32:00.617
Um...
         [laughs softly]

32:00.719 --> 32:03.453
I still can't believe
         it's happening.

32:03.555 --> 32:06.056
Anyway, I would love to
  meet you and get to know you,

32:06.158 --> 32:08.926
so, uh--and if it's easier
       if I come up to you

32:09.028 --> 32:12.696
or meet you halfway,
        just let me know.

32:12.798 --> 32:17.501
Anyway, this is my cell, uh,
  so text and call me anytime.

32:19.171 --> 32:21.271
Thanks.

32:21.373 --> 32:25.842
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:25.945 --> 32:26.843
[sighs]

32:26.946 --> 32:29.646
[cell phone ringing]

32:29.748 --> 32:31.281
This is Sarah.

32:31.383 --> 32:33.583
<i> - Hi, Sarah,</i>
     <i> this is Ann Reynolds.</i>

32:33.686 --> 32:35.152
<i> I got your message.</i>

32:35.254 --> 32:36.687
- My God, hi.

32:36.789 --> 32:38.455
I'm so sorry.
         I'm just, uh--

32:38.557 --> 32:40.590
I'm just literally
     walking into the house.

32:40.693 --> 32:42.159
<i> - Oh, I can call back if--</i>

32:42.261 --> 32:43.627
- No, no, no, not at all.

32:43.729 --> 32:45.529
Thank you so much
        for calling back.

32:45.631 --> 32:47.497
Um, listen, did, uh--

32:47.599 --> 32:49.299
did Matt have a chance
       to speak with you?

32:49.401 --> 32:51.134
<i> - I knew he'd try to find you.</i>

32:51.236 --> 32:53.603
<i> I just never believed</i>
   <i> it would actually happen.</i>

32:53.706 --> 32:55.272
- [laughs wryly]

32:55.374 --> 32:59.276
Yeah, I--I, um--
             [sighs]

32:59.378 --> 33:00.777
I don't even know
          what to say.

33:00.879 --> 33:02.980
I--I feel happy.

33:03.082 --> 33:06.850
I feel sad.
     I feel--I feel scared.

33:06.952 --> 33:08.385
- Well, of course you are.

33:08.487 --> 33:11.822
Your son just came back
         from the dead.

33:11.924 --> 33:13.857
- Right.

33:13.959 --> 33:17.194
Listen, I would
    really like to meet you.

33:17.296 --> 33:20.197
I mean, I feel like you're part
     of the family already.

33:20.299 --> 33:22.065
- I'm traveling
    for the next few months.

33:22.167 --> 33:24.201
That's why I didn't
        get your message,

33:24.303 --> 33:25.736
but I'll be back in July.

33:25.838 --> 33:27.170
We can get together then,

33:27.272 --> 33:29.239
have sort of a family
        reunion, I guess.

33:29.341 --> 33:32.642
<i> - Yeah, I would like that.</i>
            - Me too.

33:32.745 --> 33:35.812
If there's anything else
        you need, Sarah.

33:35.914 --> 33:38.415
- Actually, there is.
  Um, would you mind sending me

33:38.517 --> 33:40.817
some pictures of Matt

33:40.919 --> 33:43.153
when he was younger?

33:43.255 --> 33:44.654
I know that you're
    traveling at the moment,

33:44.757 --> 33:47.891
so you probably
     don't have many on you.

33:47.993 --> 33:50.394
Anything would be great.

33:50.496 --> 33:53.497
I just--I feel like
 there's all this time missing,

33:53.599 --> 33:55.332
<i> and it's--it's the only way</i>

33:55.434 --> 33:57.067
<i> that I can get a little piece</i>
          <i> of it back.</i>

33:57.169 --> 33:59.336
- No, of course.
       Give me your email.

33:59.438 --> 34:01.271
I'll see what I have.

34:01.373 --> 34:02.539
<i> - Okay.</i>

34:02.641 --> 34:04.341
<i> Thank you.</i>

34:04.443 --> 34:13.183
<i> [dark music]</i>

34:13.284 --> 34:16.152
<i> [soft music]</i>

34:16.255 --> 34:22.324
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:22.428 --> 34:25.462
[crying]

34:27.833 --> 34:30.367
Matt?
            [crying]

34:30.469 --> 34:32.268
Matt, are you here?

34:32.371 --> 34:34.404
- What's the matter?

34:34.505 --> 34:37.373
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

34:37.476 --> 34:44.514
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:45.250 --> 34:47.684
[sobbing]

34:50.155 --> 34:53.023
We searched for weeks.

34:56.027 --> 34:57.961
The Coast Guard had a--

34:58.063 --> 35:01.198
a dive team work
    for three days straight.

35:02.968 --> 35:06.937
The county sheriff organized
   a search through the woods.

35:08.240 --> 35:10.140
It was in every paper,

35:10.242 --> 35:13.143
every local news channel.

35:14.680 --> 35:16.646
After 72 hours I could sense

35:16.748 --> 35:20.717
that they thought
     that it was hopeless...

35:20.819 --> 35:23.887
but I didn't give up.

35:23.989 --> 35:26.289
I searched myself.

35:28.393 --> 35:31.561
I memorized
    every inch of that beach,

35:31.663 --> 35:35.465
wandering up and down,
      looking for anything.

35:35.567 --> 35:37.834
A sign.

35:37.936 --> 35:41.104
<i> [soft music]</i>

35:41.206 --> 35:43.707
The body was never recovered.

35:45.010 --> 35:48.044
The official ruling
        was lost at sea.

35:50.415 --> 35:54.518
It took a month
      before I broke down.

35:56.722 --> 35:58.522
I just--

35:58.624 --> 36:01.591
something inside me
           just died.

36:01.693 --> 36:04.594
I couldn't eat.
        I couldn't sleep.

36:04.696 --> 36:06.963
I was this...

36:07.065 --> 36:10.066
shell of a person.

36:10.169 --> 36:13.703
I was in my body,
   but my soul was just gone.

36:16.208 --> 36:18.608
And I felt so guilty.

36:21.046 --> 36:24.147
I was there.

36:24.249 --> 36:25.649
I was right there.

36:25.751 --> 36:29.219
If I had just...
   been paying more attention.

36:29.321 --> 36:32.155
If I had just been...

36:32.257 --> 36:34.491
a better mother.

36:34.593 --> 36:38.195
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:38.297 --> 36:41.932
It took me a long time
to feel something normal again.

36:43.635 --> 36:46.303
And then, slowly,

36:46.405 --> 36:50.373
this scab grew over my heart.

36:51.510 --> 36:53.543
You know?

36:55.247 --> 36:57.480
Healed...

36:57.583 --> 37:00.116
but tender.

37:05.490 --> 37:07.524
[sighs]

37:07.626 --> 37:11.294
But I still never
         forgave myself.

37:19.504 --> 37:22.639
- I forgive you.

37:22.741 --> 37:29.012
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:29.114 --> 37:31.114
- Hi.
      - Is everything okay?

37:31.216 --> 37:34.017
You sounded like
            you were in trouble.

37:34.119 --> 37:35.685
- Uh, no.

37:35.787 --> 37:39.122
Um, my detective friend
got back to me.

37:39.224 --> 37:41.858
- Uh-huh.
             - Uh...

37:41.960 --> 37:44.127
There are no records of Matt.

37:44.229 --> 37:48.098
He searched Matt, Matthew,
Reynolds, Sherwood.

37:48.200 --> 37:49.699
Nothing came up.

37:49.801 --> 37:51.601
- Well, that's--
       that's good, right?

37:51.703 --> 37:53.136
That means that
      he's not in trouble.

37:53.238 --> 37:55.305
- No, no records at all.

37:55.407 --> 37:57.941
No school records,
      no hospital records,

37:58.043 --> 38:00.043
no license at the DMV,

38:00.145 --> 38:02.779
not even a Facebook.

38:02.881 --> 38:05.982
- Um, what about St. John's,
   where they dropped him off?

38:06.084 --> 38:08.451
They must have something.
     - I called them myself.

38:08.553 --> 38:10.053
Even spoke to a nun
   who was there at the time.

38:10.155 --> 38:11.488
If a kid was dropped off,

38:11.590 --> 38:14.224
they would have
had to report it.

38:14.326 --> 38:16.259
Something doesn't add up.

38:16.361 --> 38:18.161
<i> [dark music]</i>

38:18.263 --> 38:19.663
- He is not who he says he is.

38:19.765 --> 38:22.098
- He took the DNA test.
Why would he do that?

38:22.200 --> 38:24.000
- To buy time to try
                to win you over.

38:24.102 --> 38:26.102
- For what?
        - The money, Mom!

38:26.204 --> 38:27.737
Come on, it is obvious.

38:27.839 --> 38:29.439
- You guys are gonna
be late for your dinner.

38:29.541 --> 38:30.940
- This is--this is why I knew
             I had to come here,

38:31.043 --> 38:32.275
because I knew you'd
               just blow it off.

38:32.377 --> 38:33.610
- I am not blowing
it off, Ian, okay?

38:33.712 --> 38:35.145
I am just open to the reality

38:35.247 --> 38:38.415
that nothing about
this situation is normal

38:38.517 --> 38:42.619
and that maybe, just maybe
there's another explanation.

38:42.721 --> 38:44.187
- What's going on?

38:44.289 --> 38:47.624
You guys look nice.
     What is it, date night?

38:47.726 --> 38:49.192
- It's a charity dinner.

38:49.294 --> 38:51.761
- Let's see your
     driver's license, Matt.

38:51.863 --> 38:54.197
- Ian.
         - No, come on.

38:54.299 --> 38:55.999
Let's see it.
   - What the hell's going on?

38:56.101 --> 38:58.468
- Oh, you know what's going on.

38:58.570 --> 39:00.303
Who are you?

39:00.405 --> 39:01.438
- I'm your brother.
           - Oh, yeah?

39:01.540 --> 39:02.772
Then why don't you prove it?

39:02.874 --> 39:05.642
- Look, I don't have
           to be here.

39:05.744 --> 39:07.811
- Yeah, exactly,
  so why don't you just run back

39:07.913 --> 39:09.713
to wherever you came from, huh?

39:09.815 --> 39:11.981
- What is this about?
     - We're just wondering

39:12.084 --> 39:14.017
why there are
no records of you, Matt.

39:14.119 --> 39:15.852
I had a friend of mine
run a background check.

39:15.954 --> 39:17.987
- Oh, come on.

39:18.090 --> 39:20.457
I took the stupid DNA test.

39:20.559 --> 39:21.791
I mean, what more do you want?

39:21.893 --> 39:23.560
What, do you want
               my fingerprints?

39:23.662 --> 39:25.528
- No--
  - Can I pee in a cup for you?

39:25.630 --> 39:27.831
Seriously, Mom?
 - To help us understand, Matt,

39:27.933 --> 39:30.300
were you using another name
on the license?

39:31.803 --> 39:34.237
- I don't have a license.

39:35.640 --> 39:37.640
Look for yourself.

39:38.944 --> 39:41.144
I couldn't afford a car
until recently,

39:41.246 --> 39:43.146
so I never got a license.

39:43.248 --> 39:45.215
That truck I bought
          with cash a month ago,

39:45.317 --> 39:47.083
so I never registered it.

39:47.185 --> 39:49.486
Every job that I've ever had
has been cash under the table,

39:49.588 --> 39:51.121
so I never needed
a bank account.

39:51.223 --> 39:53.223
What more do you want to know?

39:56.294 --> 39:58.595
You guys take a lot
    of this stuff for granted

39:58.697 --> 40:01.564
because you're privileged...

40:02.934 --> 40:05.835
But not everybody
        lives like this.

40:05.937 --> 40:08.805
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

40:08.907 --> 40:15.945
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:18.884 --> 40:22.552
- Doesn't prove anything.
         - We should go.

40:22.654 --> 40:25.922
- Hey, you know what I think?
    It's not about me at all.

40:26.024 --> 40:30.026
It's all about Ian
  and his big investment plan.

40:31.396 --> 40:33.263
- You don't know what
      you're talking about.

40:33.365 --> 40:35.064
- Oh, he didn't tell you.

40:35.167 --> 40:38.568
Ian is planning on buying
a company in Portland,

40:38.670 --> 40:40.937
and he hasn't even
told his partners.

40:41.039 --> 40:44.574
He wants Dad's money, our
 money, keep it all for himself

40:44.676 --> 40:47.610
so he can roll the dice on some
tech nerds with a new TV.

40:47.712 --> 40:50.280
- It's not a TV. It's--
         - Is this true?

40:50.382 --> 40:52.916
- Look, this--this is
        this new company.

40:53.018 --> 40:55.218
Nobody's ever seen anything
        like this before.

40:55.320 --> 40:56.553
- Well, I hope you guys
weren't planning on

40:56.655 --> 40:58.254
starting a family anytime soon

40:58.356 --> 41:01.491
'cause Daddy has got
all his eggs in that basket.

41:01.593 --> 41:02.592
- Ian!

41:02.694 --> 41:03.993
Matt!
           - [grunts]

41:04.095 --> 41:06.963
<i> [tense music]</i>

41:07.065 --> 41:14.137
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:15.841 --> 41:17.941
- I am your brother,

41:18.043 --> 41:21.110
and I'm entitled
to whatever that means,

41:21.213 --> 41:24.681
and I am not doing
 your stupid deal.

41:32.257 --> 41:33.756
both: Ian--
         - I'll be back.

41:33.859 --> 41:35.024
- Ian, are you okay?
      - What about dinner?

41:35.126 --> 41:36.960
- I need some air.

41:37.062 --> 41:38.595
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

41:38.697 --> 41:39.996
[engine revs]

41:40.098 --> 41:42.966
[tires squealing]

41:43.068 --> 41:50.106
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:14.132 --> 42:16.799
Come on.
            Come on!

42:24.576 --> 42:27.377
Come on!

42:29.548 --> 42:31.781
[tires squeal]
            [shouts]

42:35.453 --> 42:36.853
- All right.
Iris is responsive.

42:36.955 --> 42:38.288
Ian! Ian!

42:38.390 --> 42:40.023
You've been in
a car accident, okay?

42:40.125 --> 42:42.792
I want a full x-ray and CT scan
of the abdomen and pelvis.

42:42.894 --> 42:44.260
Let's get him on
5 milligrams of morphine.

42:44.362 --> 42:46.095
- Got it.

42:46.197 --> 42:48.598
[machine beeps, fades]

42:54.139 --> 42:56.272
- Hey.

42:56.374 --> 42:57.941
- Hi.

42:59.210 --> 43:01.611
- God, I thought I was dead.

43:01.713 --> 43:04.013
- Sounds like you
               should have been.

43:05.150 --> 43:06.883
- Ian?

43:06.985 --> 43:10.019
- Hi, Mom.
            - Hi. Hi.

43:10.121 --> 43:13.556
- They found your car
           50 feet off the road.

43:13.658 --> 43:17.026
Said you must have been
 going around that turn so fast.

43:17.128 --> 43:19.028
what happened?

43:19.130 --> 43:21.798
- I--I don't know.

43:21.900 --> 43:25.401
I--it happened so fast.

43:25.503 --> 43:27.937
I--I think lost control.

43:29.240 --> 43:31.374
- You're lucky that
the car behind you

43:31.476 --> 43:34.243
saw you go off the road.

43:34.346 --> 43:36.045
You're lucky to be alive.

43:38.149 --> 43:41.851
- They found lacerations
       on your liver and spleen,

43:41.953 --> 43:45.321
pretty serious
internal bleeding.

43:45.423 --> 43:48.758
They had to operate.
   - Am I gonna be all right?

43:48.860 --> 43:50.326
- You're gonna be
                 pretty immobile

43:50.428 --> 43:54.430
for the next six weeks,
                       but yeah.

43:54.532 --> 43:56.165
[knocks on door]

43:56.267 --> 43:59.102
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

43:59.204 --> 44:01.638
- I am so sorry.

44:02.440 --> 44:04.140
- It's okay.

44:05.677 --> 44:07.777
- No, it's not.

44:09.147 --> 44:12.015
I'm--I'm not ever
           gonna forgive myself.

44:12.117 --> 44:15.518
- I want you guys to stay
             at the house, okay?

44:15.620 --> 44:18.021
I can help out
     while Rachel's at work.

44:18.123 --> 44:19.789
- Yeah, me too.

44:19.891 --> 44:22.325
Anything I can do.

44:23.695 --> 44:25.995
- Speaking of which...
                  [laughs wryly]

44:28.333 --> 44:31.467
I'm too young to be a widow.

44:36.307 --> 44:37.974
- I'm sorry.

44:38.076 --> 44:40.643
- I'll be back
in a couple hours.

44:40.745 --> 44:42.645
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

44:42.747 --> 44:44.380
- Hey, I'll walk you out.

44:44.482 --> 44:46.516
- Matt?

44:49.487 --> 44:51.821
It's fine.
            Nothing.

44:51.923 --> 44:53.256
- All right.

44:53.358 --> 44:55.858
Well, I'll see you guys
            in a bit.

45:02.033 --> 45:04.233
- I thought I'd lost you.

45:05.603 --> 45:07.170
You and your dad
in the same month,

45:07.272 --> 45:10.139
and that would
have been too much.

45:10.241 --> 45:11.774
Too much.

45:11.876 --> 45:15.778
- Mom, there was something
             wrong with the car.

45:15.880 --> 45:18.815
I tried to slow down,
     and the brakes didn't work.

45:18.917 --> 45:21.384
There was nothing
               that I could do.

45:23.588 --> 45:26.856
That car had a full inspection
               three months ago.

45:26.958 --> 45:28.491
<i> [tense music]</i>

45:28.593 --> 45:29.992
- [sighs]

45:30.095 --> 45:32.395
- Mom.
             - Yeah?

45:33.932 --> 45:36.032
- What if it wasn't
                    an accident?

45:39.771 --> 45:42.672
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

45:42.774 --> 45:44.974
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

45:45.076 --> 45:47.443
[cell phone beeping]

45:49.781 --> 45:53.182
- Hi, uh, is this
         D & D Salvage?

45:53.284 --> 45:55.451
Okay, I'm calling about a car

45:55.553 --> 45:57.620
that was totaled
       about a month ago.

45:57.722 --> 46:01.758
Yeah, it was, um,
      a Jaguar, dark green.

46:03.828 --> 46:06.162
It was my husband's car.

46:06.264 --> 46:07.663
Mm-hmm.

46:07.766 --> 46:10.500
You--you sold it?

46:10.602 --> 46:12.435
To who?

46:13.938 --> 46:15.972
Right, well, I mean,
  even if you sold it for cash,

46:16.074 --> 46:18.141
I'm sure that you guys must
 have some kind of record there

46:18.243 --> 46:20.543
at the sh--

46:20.645 --> 46:22.845
oh.

46:22.947 --> 46:24.914
I see.

46:26.151 --> 46:27.884
Okay.

46:27.986 --> 46:30.887
[sighs deeply]

46:30.989 --> 46:38.060
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

47:14.499 --> 47:16.933
Ian was in an accident.

47:17.035 --> 47:19.368
- Oh, my God.

47:19.470 --> 47:21.904
Is he okay?
         - Yeah, barely.

47:22.006 --> 47:26.309
He--he thinks that Matt might
  have something to do with it.

47:26.411 --> 47:29.045
- What? Why?
         - I don't know.

47:29.147 --> 47:33.449
I--I mean, I feel like maybe
       there is something wrong.

47:33.551 --> 47:36.152
- This whole thing
is just insane.

47:36.254 --> 47:37.753
It's just--you know,

47:37.856 --> 47:40.790
anyone in your position
would feel crazy right now.

47:40.892 --> 47:44.293
- I don't know what's worse.

47:44.395 --> 47:46.596
If it's not him
  and I'm living with a stranger

47:46.698 --> 47:48.464
or if it is him

47:48.566 --> 47:52.335
and it's my fault
           that he's a stranger.

47:52.437 --> 47:54.470
- You know what I think?
I think

47:54.572 --> 47:58.074
that Matt is your son

47:58.176 --> 48:00.509
and that all you can do
is love him

48:00.612 --> 48:04.780
and try to help Ian cope
as best as you can.

48:04.883 --> 48:06.916
It's gonna be hard
for everybody, right?

48:07.018 --> 48:09.118
But you are one of
the strongest women

48:09.220 --> 48:11.754
I've ever met in my life.

48:12.857 --> 48:15.258
- Thank you.

48:15.360 --> 48:16.792
I needed that.

48:16.895 --> 48:23.933
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

48:32.143 --> 48:36.012
Hey, um, did you see
      Karen the other day?

48:36.114 --> 48:37.847
- Who?
   - Karen, my sister-in-law,

48:37.949 --> 48:40.850
she was supposed to stop by,
 but I didn't hear from her.

48:40.952 --> 48:44.287
I left a key for her
       under the doormat.

48:44.389 --> 48:46.289
- No, you know, there was
      a key left on the counter.

48:46.391 --> 48:47.890
I thought maybe you left
           it there for someone.

48:47.992 --> 48:50.826
You know, I could go get it.
       - No, that's okay.

48:50.929 --> 48:52.895
She probably
just didn't like it.

48:52.997 --> 48:55.197
- Her loss.

48:55.300 --> 49:02.371
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

49:14.719 --> 49:18.187
- Your mom said to use these.

49:18.289 --> 49:20.623
- Thanks.

49:29.267 --> 49:30.733
Oh, you don't--
      you don't have to do that.

49:30.835 --> 49:33.803
- Ian's asleep.
I stay up late.

49:33.905 --> 49:36.706
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

49:36.808 --> 49:38.674
- Thanks.

49:45.550 --> 49:47.383
Hey.

49:48.186 --> 49:51.287
I'm sorry again.

49:51.389 --> 49:53.923
- Ian's got a temper.
[laughs softly]

49:54.025 --> 49:56.325
It's no surprise.

49:56.427 --> 49:57.994
He's taken off
like that before,

49:58.096 --> 50:01.564
and every time it scares
the hell out of me.

50:03.101 --> 50:04.533
- Yeah.

50:07.772 --> 50:10.706
But I pushed him.

50:13.177 --> 50:14.777
- Are you really Matt?

50:17.615 --> 50:19.448
- Yeah.

50:19.550 --> 50:26.589
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

50:27.458 --> 50:29.959
- Did you come back
for the money?

50:32.563 --> 50:34.196
- Yeah.

50:35.133 --> 50:37.099
At first.

50:39.804 --> 50:42.438
I saw his obituary
          in the paper.

50:42.540 --> 50:47.143
I mean, his face
             had barely changed.

50:47.245 --> 50:50.246
I knew he was my dad.

50:50.348 --> 50:54.216
All these years, I thought
       that they'd abandoned me.

50:54.318 --> 50:58.487
I find out he's
      a successful business guy.

50:58.589 --> 51:01.157
Gotta be leaving behind
                    a few bucks.

51:01.259 --> 51:04.660
I mean, yeah,
     I'm gonna take what's mine.

51:06.497 --> 51:10.332
But then...

51:10.435 --> 51:12.368
I meet her

51:12.470 --> 51:14.403
and Ian

51:14.505 --> 51:17.840
and...you.

51:18.976 --> 51:22.411
And--and somehow it's like
             all that bitterness

51:22.513 --> 51:25.181
and...betrayal,

51:25.283 --> 51:28.951
it--it's like
         it's just melting away.

51:30.354 --> 51:33.989
This is the first time
            in a long, long time

51:34.092 --> 51:38.260
where something
              feels right to me.

51:42.033 --> 51:44.433
- Ian'll come around.

51:47.572 --> 51:49.672
You good?

51:50.541 --> 51:52.808
- Thanks for the helping...

51:52.910 --> 51:54.443
and for listening.

51:54.545 --> 51:56.712
- [laughs softly]

51:56.814 --> 51:59.381
- Ian is a lucky guy.

52:02.987 --> 52:04.520
- Goodnight.

52:04.622 --> 52:06.689
- Night.

52:12.630 --> 52:16.065
[sighs]

52:28.179 --> 52:32.314
- Hey. Sorry, uh,
can you help me for a sec?

52:35.553 --> 52:38.154
I know this is awkward,
  but he's loopy on the drugs,

52:38.256 --> 52:41.257
and I can't lift him by myself.
     - No, it's no problem.

52:42.260 --> 52:44.260
Hey, Ian.

52:47.932 --> 52:49.465
- No, stop, leave me alone.

52:49.567 --> 52:50.633
- Come here.
              - No.

52:50.735 --> 52:52.601
- Hey, hey, don't worry.

52:52.703 --> 52:59.542
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

52:59.644 --> 53:02.411
<i> [dark music]</i>

53:02.513 --> 53:09.552
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

53:16.093 --> 53:18.093
- Thank you.

53:23.768 --> 53:26.268
Sorry, I'm--I'm gonna grab some
towels from out of the dryer.

53:26.370 --> 53:28.704
Can you watch him
for a sec?

54:31.969 --> 54:34.069
Okay, got some nice, clean--
             [gasps]

54:34.171 --> 54:35.904
- Oh, you all right
         there brother.

54:36.007 --> 54:37.706
You're okay.
You're okay.

54:37.808 --> 54:39.141
- [coughing]
    - Are--are you all right?

54:39.243 --> 54:40.542
- He must have slipped under.

54:40.645 --> 54:41.877
I just got up
to dry off my hands,

54:41.979 --> 54:42.945
and when I got back,
he was under.

54:43.047 --> 54:44.246
I thought he was joking.

54:44.348 --> 54:46.048
- I probably filled it
up too high.

54:46.150 --> 54:48.550
- No, I--I should have stayed
         put until you got back.

54:48.653 --> 54:50.119
Those drugs
            are heavy-duty, huh?

54:50.221 --> 54:53.956
- Yeah. I had no idea
how out of it he'd be.

54:54.058 --> 54:56.225
- Well, I'm gonna get back
                  to the dishes.

54:56.327 --> 54:58.627
You got it from here?

54:58.729 --> 55:01.630
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

55:01.732 --> 55:03.332
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

55:03.434 --> 55:05.000
- I was out of the room
            for, like, a minute.

55:05.102 --> 55:06.602
When I came back,
      he was already pulling you

55:06.704 --> 55:08.070
out of the water.
  - I'm telling you what I saw.

55:08.172 --> 55:09.438
- You're on drugs, babe.

55:09.540 --> 55:11.940
- I--I know what happened.

55:12.043 --> 55:14.743
- He's trying, okay?

55:14.845 --> 55:17.946
And you're making it
                 very difficult.

55:18.049 --> 55:21.050
Maybe you should give him
                 another chance.

55:25.289 --> 55:26.755
Hey.

55:28.626 --> 55:30.025
I love you.

55:31.996 --> 55:33.595
- I love you too.

55:37.234 --> 55:39.268
- Don't you like
                 this nightgown?

55:42.206 --> 55:44.039
- It's nice.

55:44.141 --> 55:46.208
Covers a bit too much though.

55:46.310 --> 55:48.777
- [laughs softly]
There he is.

55:48.879 --> 55:51.747
- [chuckles softly]

55:54.418 --> 55:59.088
You know, the doctor didn't say
           no physical activity.

56:01.092 --> 56:03.359
- No, he didn't.
            - Hm-mm.

56:03.461 --> 56:10.532
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

56:12.636 --> 56:15.504
<i> [dark music]</i>

56:15.606 --> 56:22.644
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

56:30.588 --> 56:32.454
<i> [phone line ringing]</i>

56:35.526 --> 56:38.093
- These are done.
          - Oh, great.

56:38.195 --> 56:39.762
Hey, Kare, it's me.
           I just wanted to know

56:39.864 --> 56:42.598
if you got my message
           about dinner tonight.

56:42.700 --> 56:45.567
Miss you bunches.
                            Bye.

56:45.669 --> 56:47.336
- Oh, I, uh--I forgot
to tell you.

56:47.438 --> 56:48.804
She, uh--she dropped
by the other day.

56:48.906 --> 56:50.472
- Karen? Really?

56:50.574 --> 56:52.474
- Yeah, um, I'm--I'm so sorry.

56:52.576 --> 56:55.477
I--it's just--it's--I mean,
it's been so crazy around here.

56:55.579 --> 56:57.479
She wanted to apologize
for not meeting you.

56:57.581 --> 56:58.981
- Hmm, yeah.

56:59.083 --> 57:00.649
I, uh--I waited for her
                   the other day

57:00.751 --> 57:03.118
for, like, a half an hour,
        and she never showed up,

57:03.220 --> 57:04.820
completely flaked.

57:04.922 --> 57:06.989
- She said something about,
like, going on a business trip

57:07.091 --> 57:09.925
for the next couple weeks.
She was kind of in a hurry.

57:10.027 --> 57:11.794
I'm--I'm sorry
I forgot to mention it.

57:11.896 --> 57:13.128
- No, it's fine.

57:13.230 --> 57:14.830
I love her,
        but if there's one thing

57:14.932 --> 57:16.432
you'll learn
           about your Aunt Karen

57:16.534 --> 57:17.966
is she can be a handful.

57:18.068 --> 57:19.935
- Hey, talking about me again?

57:20.037 --> 57:22.371
- You, my dear,
     are anything but a handful.

57:22.473 --> 57:23.872
- Sorry I'm late.

57:23.974 --> 57:25.774
- And I think we're
             almost ready, guys.

57:25.876 --> 57:27.342
Will you put those out
      on the patio table for me?

57:27.445 --> 57:28.510
- Yes.
       - And get to work.

57:28.612 --> 57:30.179
I'm still crippled here.

57:30.281 --> 57:31.680
- Oh, I'm not gonna let you
      play the victim card

57:31.782 --> 57:33.115
for very much longer.

57:33.217 --> 57:35.851
- Love you.
           <i> [laughter]</i>

57:35.953 --> 57:38.987
- So what's going on
with all of dad's stuff?

57:39.089 --> 57:40.789
I mean, they said,
like, a month.

57:40.891 --> 57:41.990
That's next week, right?

57:42.092 --> 57:44.359
- I don't know.
              Um...

57:44.462 --> 57:46.328
I know they paid off
all the outstanding debt,

57:46.430 --> 57:47.796
so we just have
          to make a tax payment,

57:47.898 --> 57:49.031
and we should be fine.

57:49.133 --> 57:52.301
That should be it.
              Yeah.

57:52.403 --> 57:55.304
- Well, what about the,
        um--the DNA test?

57:55.406 --> 57:58.240
I mean, we should have
 heard something by now, right?

57:58.342 --> 58:01.210
- Um...

58:01.312 --> 58:03.011
yeah, um, I'm going to,

58:03.113 --> 58:05.481
uh, follow up with them
tomorrow and just,

58:05.583 --> 58:08.150
you know, see if...

58:08.252 --> 58:12.054
maybe they're backed up
or something.

58:12.156 --> 58:13.689
- Pool looks great, Mom.
          - Thank you.

58:13.791 --> 58:15.858
- Yeah.
   - Matt helped me clean it.

58:15.960 --> 58:18.293
- Mm, she did all
    the smart chemical stuff.

58:18.395 --> 58:20.662
I just scooped out the crap.

58:23.701 --> 58:25.567
- Hey, what do you say,

58:25.669 --> 58:27.870
after dinner
            we jump in the pool,

58:27.972 --> 58:30.906
do a little Marco Polo
         like the good old days?

58:31.008 --> 58:32.908
- Oh, yeah, yeah,
   we used to love that, huh?

58:33.010 --> 58:35.377
- Yeah, yeah.
    It wasn't Marco Polo, right?

58:35.479 --> 58:38.046
You called it something else.
                    What was it?

58:38.148 --> 58:39.882
- I don't know.
     - No, no, no, come on.

58:39.984 --> 58:43.252
It was, like--it was, like,
   your favorite Ninja Turtle.

58:43.354 --> 58:46.255
Marco.
                        Come on.

58:46.357 --> 58:48.790
Marco, and...

58:48.893 --> 58:50.592
- Sorry.

58:50.694 --> 58:52.694
I don't remember that one.

58:52.796 --> 58:55.797
I mean, I guess it was
a long time ago, right?

58:55.900 --> 58:58.767
<i> [tense music]</i>

58:58.869 --> 59:05.941
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

59:25.763 --> 59:29.598
[cell phone beeping]

59:29.700 --> 59:32.100
<i> - The number you have reached</i>
       <i> is not in service.</i>

59:32.202 --> 59:34.970
<i> Please check the number</i>
     <i> or try your call aga--</i>

59:38.075 --> 59:40.442
<i> - There's no results for</i>
  <i> Ann Reynolds in Connecticut.</i>

59:40.544 --> 59:41.777
There's no Facebook.

59:41.879 --> 59:43.345
There's no
          business associations.

59:43.447 --> 59:45.414
The phone is
           no longer in service.

59:45.516 --> 59:48.116
- Why would he lie about that?
    - I searched the number,

59:48.218 --> 59:49.751
and it seems like
        some kind of burner line

59:49.853 --> 59:51.954
with no address listed.

59:52.056 --> 59:54.489
[sighs]
          Your detective friend,

59:54.592 --> 59:57.526
do you think that he can
            do us another favor?

01:00:01.365 --> 01:00:03.365
[car approaching]

01:00:07.037 --> 01:00:09.504
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:00:09.607 --> 01:00:13.375
[car door closes]

01:00:13.477 --> 01:00:15.043
Something wrong with it?

01:00:15.145 --> 01:00:18.480
- Ah, fan belt snapped,
     so I had to replace it,

01:00:18.582 --> 01:00:21.984
and then I found corrosion
       on the battery terminals.

01:00:22.086 --> 01:00:24.453
You know, she's old,

01:00:24.555 --> 01:00:27.222
so nothing's perfect.

01:00:27.324 --> 01:00:29.057
- You seem pretty handy
for someone who's never

01:00:29.159 --> 01:00:31.560
had a license before.

01:00:31.662 --> 01:00:33.195
- Yeah, uh, look,

01:00:33.297 --> 01:00:35.030
I'm gonna get all that
                     sorted out.

01:00:35.132 --> 01:00:37.633
Don't worry.

01:00:37.735 --> 01:00:39.468
- Listen, I called
the testing facility,

01:00:39.570 --> 01:00:43.572
and there was
a contamination in the lab.

01:00:43.674 --> 01:00:47.342
Um, the results
are inconclusive.

01:00:47.444 --> 01:00:49.177
They apologized,
but it looks like

01:00:49.279 --> 01:00:51.346
we're gonna have
to do the test again.

01:00:51.448 --> 01:00:54.516
They promised to expedite it.

01:00:54.618 --> 01:00:56.051
I know it's annoying.

01:00:56.153 --> 01:00:58.220
I'm sorry.

01:00:58.322 --> 01:01:01.189
- No, it's fine.

01:01:01.291 --> 01:01:02.991
Just leave it inside.

01:01:03.093 --> 01:01:05.594
I'll do it.

01:01:13.771 --> 01:01:16.171
<i> [cell phone ringing]</i>

01:01:17.441 --> 01:01:19.007
- Hey.

01:01:19.109 --> 01:01:20.776
<i> - Hey, I got a hit</i>
     <i> on your license plate.</i>

01:01:20.878 --> 01:01:22.878
<i> Uh, it's registered</i>
      <i> to a Jessica Parker.</i>

01:01:22.980 --> 01:01:25.347
- Anything on her?
         <i> - Usual stuff.</i>

01:01:25.449 --> 01:01:28.550
<i> Speeding tickets,</i>
    <i> some financial problems.</i>

01:01:28.652 --> 01:01:30.185
<i> That's probably why</i>
      <i> she sold the truck.</i>

01:01:30.287 --> 01:01:32.921
- Yeah, maybe.

01:01:33.023 --> 01:01:35.190
You got an address?

01:01:35.292 --> 01:01:42.330
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:01:45.803 --> 01:01:48.136
Where the hell
         is this place?

01:02:30.247 --> 01:02:37.285
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:02:46.163 --> 01:02:48.930
[truck door closes,
       engine turns over]

01:02:49.032 --> 01:02:56.104
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:03:11.255 --> 01:03:14.556
- [yelps, muffled screams]

01:03:14.658 --> 01:03:16.224
- [grunts]

01:03:33.911 --> 01:03:36.945
- Rachel, hey, listen,

01:03:37.047 --> 01:03:38.446
I'm doing something
         really stupid,

01:03:38.549 --> 01:03:40.515
and I wanted to tell someone.

01:04:01.638 --> 01:04:04.639
- Mom?

01:04:04.741 --> 01:04:06.641
What's going on?

01:04:06.743 --> 01:04:08.844
- Don't worry.
  I'm taking care of something.

01:04:11.248 --> 01:04:13.448
I love you.
         Go back inside.

01:04:13.550 --> 01:04:19.487
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:04:19.590 --> 01:04:20.989
[tires squeal]

01:04:21.091 --> 01:04:22.424
- [grunts]

01:04:42.145 --> 01:04:44.045
- [grunting]

01:04:44.147 --> 01:04:47.215
[muffled shouting]

01:04:51.555 --> 01:04:58.493
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:05:51.915 --> 01:05:52.814
- She wants me
        to do this again.

01:05:52.916 --> 01:05:54.482
- Why?
            - [gasps]

01:05:54.584 --> 01:05:56.451
- I thought you said
   you had this under control.

01:05:56.553 --> 01:05:59.888
I need the money,
   or I'm gonna lose my house.

01:06:02.659 --> 01:06:05.527
<i> [waves crashing]</i>

01:06:05.629 --> 01:06:12.667
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:06:19.076 --> 01:06:20.675
- The test came
back inconclusive.

01:06:20.777 --> 01:06:24.079
Once that's settled,
we get the money.

01:06:24.181 --> 01:06:25.747
Just be patient.

01:06:25.849 --> 01:06:28.483
- I'm done being patient.

01:06:28.585 --> 01:06:30.952
- Where's the kid?

01:06:31.054 --> 01:06:38.093
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:06:45.869 --> 01:06:48.236
- Come on.

01:06:55.812 --> 01:06:57.278
- Hey.

01:06:58.081 --> 01:07:00.315
Hey. Hey.

01:07:00.417 --> 01:07:02.217
Come here.

01:07:03.553 --> 01:07:05.954
Open your mouth.

01:07:07.724 --> 01:07:09.090
- Oh.

01:07:14.464 --> 01:07:16.364
- Jessie!
         - Who was that?

01:07:16.466 --> 01:07:21.336
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:07:21.438 --> 01:07:22.871
- [shrieks]

01:07:22.973 --> 01:07:25.974
[both grunting]

01:07:26.943 --> 01:07:28.276
Sarah!

01:07:28.378 --> 01:07:31.413
[gunshots]

01:07:34.751 --> 01:07:37.786
- [grunting]

01:07:40.724 --> 01:07:43.758
[muffled shouting]

01:07:46.630 --> 01:07:53.668
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:08:09.853 --> 01:08:16.925
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:08:25.135 --> 01:08:27.102
[strains]

01:08:31.841 --> 01:08:38.880
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:08:51.027 --> 01:08:54.062
- [breathing heavily]

01:08:59.069 --> 01:09:01.970
- [grunting]

01:09:02.072 --> 01:09:04.939
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:09:05.041 --> 01:09:07.675
[growls]

01:09:20.790 --> 01:09:22.457
- Where the hell is she?
      - Hey, you're the one

01:09:22.559 --> 01:09:23.957
who let her get away.
   - You're the one who messed

01:09:24.060 --> 01:09:26.828
this whole thing up.
                Now go find her.

01:09:26.930 --> 01:09:34.002
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:09:38.908 --> 01:09:41.943
- [grunting]

01:09:50.053 --> 01:09:52.120
[squeals]
        [glass shatters]

01:09:52.221 --> 01:09:55.056
[exhales]

01:09:56.693 --> 01:09:59.761
- [breathing shakily]

01:10:04.234 --> 01:10:07.101
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

01:10:07.204 --> 01:10:13.775
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:10:13.877 --> 01:10:16.711
- [whispers] Jake.
     - Who the hell are you?

01:10:18.715 --> 01:10:20.381
Wait, stop, don't.

01:10:20.483 --> 01:10:22.517
- Matt.

01:10:23.887 --> 01:10:25.620
- How do you know my name?

01:10:26.957 --> 01:10:29.324
- It's me.

01:10:29.426 --> 01:10:30.692
It's Sarah.

01:10:30.794 --> 01:10:31.993
- No, stop.
Stay right there.

01:10:32.095 --> 01:10:35.263
- I'm your mother.

01:10:35.365 --> 01:10:37.398
- What? How?

01:10:40.637 --> 01:10:43.371
- Do you remember the beach?

01:10:43.473 --> 01:10:45.073
You and me

01:10:45.175 --> 01:10:47.342
and your dad

01:10:47.444 --> 01:10:49.577
and Ian.

01:10:49.679 --> 01:10:50.812
Do you remember?

01:10:50.914 --> 01:10:55.516
- One, two, three, four.

01:10:55.619 --> 01:10:56.818
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

01:10:56.920 --> 01:10:58.820
21, 22,

01:10:58.922 --> 01:11:00.888
23, 24,

01:11:00.991 --> 01:11:03.191
25, 26,

01:11:03.293 --> 01:11:05.126
27, 28,

01:11:05.228 --> 01:11:07.795
29, 30.

01:11:16.139 --> 01:11:18.840
[footsteps approaching]

01:11:18.942 --> 01:11:20.742
- Excuse me.

01:11:22.045 --> 01:11:23.811
Can you help me with something?

01:11:25.115 --> 01:11:31.619
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:11:33.690 --> 01:11:36.524
- It's me, Matty.

01:11:36.626 --> 01:11:38.926
It's Mom.

01:11:40.130 --> 01:11:42.864
- They told me you were dead.

01:11:42.966 --> 01:11:45.233
- Stop right there!

01:11:45.335 --> 01:11:46.434
- Jessie!

01:11:46.536 --> 01:11:48.369
- Don't try anything stupid,
Sarah.

01:11:48.471 --> 01:11:49.971
Baby.

01:11:50.073 --> 01:11:52.940
<i> [tense music]</i>

01:11:53.043 --> 01:11:58.813
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:11:58.915 --> 01:12:00.548
<i> [dial tone]</i>

01:12:00.650 --> 01:12:02.116
<i> [beeping]</i>

01:12:03.887 --> 01:12:05.620
<i> - 911, please hold.</i>

01:12:07.057 --> 01:12:09.290
- I just don't understand.

01:12:09.392 --> 01:12:11.526
Why?

01:12:12.295 --> 01:12:13.461
- Jake.

01:12:25.942 --> 01:12:27.809
Jake was mine.

01:12:27.911 --> 01:12:29.243
He was my high school
sweetheart,

01:12:29.346 --> 01:12:30.411
and then he betrayed me.

01:12:30.513 --> 01:12:31.779
- So you took our son?

01:12:31.881 --> 01:12:33.414
- You didn't deserve him!

01:12:33.516 --> 01:12:35.516
He sh--

01:12:37.921 --> 01:12:40.588
he should have
          been my son.

01:12:40.690 --> 01:12:43.191
They both should
         have been mine.

01:12:43.293 --> 01:12:44.692
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:12:44.794 --> 01:12:47.795
I saw you on the beach
            that day,

01:12:47.897 --> 01:12:49.997
your easy,
perfect life.

01:12:50.100 --> 01:12:52.600
No appreciation
for your privilege.

01:12:52.702 --> 01:12:55.837
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:12:55.939 --> 01:12:58.239
You weren't even
        paying attention.

01:13:01.211 --> 01:13:03.311
If you were the mother
         Matt deserved,

01:13:03.413 --> 01:13:05.680
he wouldn't have been taken.

01:13:06.950 --> 01:13:08.316
- And Ian?

01:13:08.418 --> 01:13:10.618
You tried to kill him
                 just like Jake?

01:13:10.720 --> 01:13:12.220
- He is not who he says he is.

01:13:12.322 --> 01:13:14.555
- He took the DNA test.
      Why would he do that?

01:13:14.657 --> 01:13:16.657
- To buy time to try
                to win you over.

01:13:16.760 --> 01:13:18.559
- For what?
        - The money, Mom!

01:13:18.661 --> 01:13:20.328
Come on, it is obvious.

01:13:20.430 --> 01:13:22.330
[latch pops]

01:13:22.432 --> 01:13:26.134
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:13:26.236 --> 01:13:28.236
- They were in the way,

01:13:28.338 --> 01:13:31.506
just like your miserable
                  sister-in-law.

